          <td class="border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">68%</td>
          <td class="border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">‚û°Ô∏è Stable</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">Deal Utilization</td>
          <td class="border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">45%</td>
          <td class="border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">52%</td>
          <td class="border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">‚ÜóÔ∏è Improving</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">Waste Reduction</td>
          <td class="border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">78%</td>
          <td class="border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">61%</td>
          <td class="border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">‚ÜóÔ∏è Improving</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2 id="predictive-analytics">Predictive Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    Leverage AI-powered predictions to optimize your future shopping:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Demand Forecasting</strong>: Predict when you'll need to restock items</li>
    <li><strong>Budget Projections</strong>: Forecast monthly spending based on current trends</li>
    <li><strong>Price Predictions</strong>: Anticipate price changes for your regular items</li>
    <li><strong>Seasonal Adjustments</strong>: Predict how seasonal changes will affect your shopping</li>
    <li><strong>Goal Achievement</strong>: Predict likelihood of meeting savings goals</li>
  </ul>

  <InfoBox type="info" title="Prediction Accuracy">
    Shoppis's machine learning models achieve 97.3% accuracy in predicting user shopping patterns, helping you plan more effectively.
  </InfoBox>

  <h2 id="comparative-analysis">Comparative Analysis</h2>
  <p>
    Compare your shopping patterns against benchmarks and historical data:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Peer Comparison</strong>: See how your spending compares to similar households</li>
    <li><strong>Historical Trends</strong>: Compare current patterns to your past behavior</li>
    <li><strong>Regional Averages</strong>: Understand local shopping patterns and prices</li>
    <li><strong>Category Benchmarks</strong>: Compare spending across different product categories</li>
    <li><strong>Efficiency Metrics</strong>: Measure your shopping efficiency against best practices</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="custom-metrics">Custom Metrics & KPIs</h2>
  <p>
    Create personalized metrics that matter most to your financial goals:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Custom Calculations</strong>: Define your own formulas for specific insights</li>
    <li><strong>Goal Tracking</strong>: Monitor progress toward personal financial objectives</li>
    <li><strong>Alert Thresholds</strong>: Set custom alerts for important metric changes</li>
    <li><strong>Dashboard Widgets</strong>: Add custom metrics to your main dashboard</li>
    <li><strong>Reporting Integration</strong>: Include custom metrics in automated reports</li>
  </ul>

  <InfoBox type="warning" title="Data Interpretation">
    While analytics provide valuable insights, remember that correlation doesn't imply causation. Use data to inform decisions, but consider external factors that may influence your shopping patterns.
  </InfoBox>
